# {{ app_title }}

Cloudflare Worker that serves [Better Auth](https://better-auth.com) and a shadcn/ui login SPA, backed by [Cloudflare D1](https://developers.cloudflare.com/d1/). Generated from the [cloudflare-better-auth-d1 copier template](https://copier.readthedocs.io/).

- Hono Worker with Better Auth mounted at `/api/auth/*`, `drizzle-orm/d1` adapter
- Vite React SPA served via the Worker's `assets` binding, gated so `/api/*` runs on the Worker
- Generated drizzle schema + SQL migration for the four better-auth tables

## Quickstart

```bash
# 1. Authenticate wrangler (one-time)
bunx wrangler login

# 2. Create the D1 database and paste the returned database_id into wrangler.jsonc
bunx wrangler d1 create {{ d1_database_name }}

# 3. Local secrets
cat > .dev.vars <<EOF
BETTER_AUTH_URL=http://localhost:8787
BETTER_AUTH_SECRET=$(openssl rand -base64 32)
EOF

# 4. Apply the initial migration locally
bun run db:migrate:local

# 5. Run
bun run dev                   # http://localhost:8787
```

## Commands

| Command | What it does |
|---|---|
| `bun run dev` | `wrangler dev` — Worker + local D1 + SPA dist |
| `bun run deploy` | `wrangler deploy` |
| `bun run typecheck` | `tsc --noEmit` against the generated Env types |
| `bun run cf-typegen` | regenerate `worker-configuration.d.ts` after wrangler.jsonc edits |
| `bun run auth:generate` | re-emit `src/db/schema.ts` from `better-auth.config.ts` |
| `bun run db:generate` | drizzle-kit migration from the new schema |
| `bun run db:migrate:local` | apply migrations to the local D1 |
| `bun run db:migrate:remote` | apply migrations to the remote D1 |
| `cd web && bun run build` | build the SPA into `web/dist` — **required before `wrangler dev` or `wrangler deploy`** |

## Deploy

```bash
bunx wrangler d1 migrations apply {{ d1_database_name }} --remote
bunx wrangler secret put BETTER_AUTH_SECRET            # paste openssl rand -base64 32
cd web && bun run build && cd ..
bunx wrangler deploy
# After first deploy: update vars.BETTER_AUTH_URL in wrangler.jsonc to the *.workers.dev URL, then redeploy.
```

See `CLAUDE.md` for the full architecture, schema-generation flow, and auth-specific gotchas.
